DataElement.preferredName: Medical Condition Performed Observation Outcome Data ISO21090.ANY.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Any sign, symptom, disease, or other medical occurrence. EXAMPLE(S): death, back pain, headache, pulmonary embolism, heart attack, pregnancy, flu, broken bone, menstrual period, depression OTHER NAME(S): Clinical Events, Medical History NOTE(S): This condition may have been recalled by the subject or a caregiver or provided in their medical record. Data or information that is determined by an act of observation. EXAMPLE(S): (1) The result of a lab test, physical finding, self-reported symptom. (2) The adverse event term code.
